      .subsection
        h2 The Legwork Smile
        p Sometimes, it may be preferred to use the Legwork “Smile” on it’s own, rather than the full logo: predominately, when the Legwork brand has already been established through the use of the full logo, copy, or vocally.
        p Futhermore, there are instances where we may want to use the Legwork Smile independently, such as apparel, stickers, or other merchandise– instances where we want the graphics to be the main point of focus, and the icon to act as a visual reminder.
        .one-column-image-container
          img(src="https://github.com/LegworkPRM/style-guide/blob/master/img/lw-icon.jpg?raw=true", alt="Legwork Logo Icon")
      .subsection
        h2 Exclusion Zone
        p To ensure legibility, our logo must stand out among other elements.  This is achieved by surrounding our logo with clear space.  The logo and the smile icon’s exclusion zone is equal to half the height of the icon (marked as × in the diagram).
        .exclusion-zone-image-container
          img(src="https://github.com/LegworkPRM/style-guide/blob/master/img/logo-exclusion-zone.png?raw=true", alt="Legwork Logo Clear Space")
          img(src="https://github.com/LegworkPRM/style-guide/blob/master/img/smile-exclusion-zone.png?raw=true", alt="Legwork Smile Icon Clear Space")
      .subsection
        h2 Minimum Size
        p Never reduce the Logo or Smile to a size smaller that the following recommendations, as it can result in loss of readibility and impact.
