      .subsection
        h2 What to Avoid
        p There are endless possbilities when it comes to color, which also means there are endless “don’ts.” A general rule of thumb is to never use color on color. If you’re using a colored background, don’t use colored text or icons.
        ul.color-info-card-grid
          li.info-card
            .color-card-name.color-card-image-with-text
            .color-card-description
              h3 Color text on Color Background
              p Don’t use color on top of color. If you have a colored background, use white text.
          li.info-card
            .color-card-name.color-card-image-with-icon
            .color-card-description
              h3 Color Icons on Color Background
              p Same with icons, use white icons if you have a colored background.        
  section.guides#type
    .section-content
      h2 Type
      p Consistent typography is a critical tool for the Legwork brand. We use two main font families: Avenir for digital and print and Proxima Nova for Web.
      .type-col-grid
        .type-col-block.font-regular
          p Proxima Nova Regular<br/>abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
        .type-col-block.font-medium
          p Proxima Nova Medium<br/>abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
        .type-col-block.font-bold
          p Proxima Nova Bold<br/>abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
        .type-col-block.font-heavy
          p Proxima Nova Heavy<br/>abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz<br/>ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ
      .subsection
        h2 General Typography Rules
        p Tracking (letter-spacing) and leading (line-height) both play crucial roles in creating the spacious and professional look throughout Legwork’s content. Be sure to give text plenty of breathing room; but, be cognizant of how you use it. A few things to watch out for:
        ul.general-list
          li Don't write headings, CTA's, links, or body copy in all caps or smallcaps
          li Never justify text
          li Don't alter the widths of letters
          li Only use brand-approved fonts
