      .subsection
        h2 Overlays in Use
        p Overlays, when executed correctly, can add value and human connection. Please adhere to the guidelines below to ensure proper usage:
        .two-col-flex-container#overlays-in-use
          .two-col-flex-item.approved-overlays
            .two-col-image-wrapper
              img(src="https://github.com/LegworkPRM/style-guide/blob/master/img/overlays-in-use-01.png?raw=true", alt="Legwork Good Overlay Usage")
            ul.general-list
              li Do use white text and CTA's on overlays
              li Do make sure there's plenty of room for text
              li Do maintain the integrity of the image
              li Do bring down the saturation to near black and white behind the overlay
          .two-col-flex-item.denied-overlays
            .two-col-image-wrapper
              img(src="https://github.com/LegworkPRM/style-guide/blob/master/img/overlays-in-use-02.png?raw=true", alt="Legwork Poor Overlay Usage")
            ul.general-list
              li Don't use color on color
              li Don't crop or distort the photo in a way that cuts off faces
              li Don't choose a photo that's too busy with faces
              li Don't bring up the saturation behind the overlay
